wer charity single|Bridge over Troubled Water]]\"<br><span style=\"font-size: 85%;\">(as part of [[Bridge over Troubled Water (song)#Artists for Grenfell Tower charity single|Artists for Grenfell]])</span>\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2017\n| 1 || 53 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || 1 || 28 || \u2014\n|\n* BPI: Silver<ref name=\"BPI\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[I Know You (Craig David song)|I Know You]]\"<br><span style=\"font-size: 85%;\">([[Craig David]] featuring Bastille)</span>\n| 5 || \u2014 || 66 || 92 || 30 || 2 || 65 || 12\n|\n* BPI: Platinum<ref name=\"BPI\"/>\n| ''[[The Time Is Now (album)|The Time Is Now]]''\n|-\n| colspan=\"12\" style=\"font-size:90%\"| \"\u2014\" denotes a recording that did not chart or was not released in that territory.\n|}\n\n===Promotional singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:5em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:1em;\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Hangin'\"\n| 2015\n| ''Doom Days (This Got Out of Hand)''\n|}\n\n==Other charted songs==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of other charted songs, with selected chart positions, showing year released and album name\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:19em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:1em;\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"7\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[UK Singles Chart|UK]]<br><ref>Peak chart positions for other charted songs in the United Kingdom:\n* \"bad_news\", \"Fake It\" and \"World Gone Mad\": {{cite web | url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/7574/bastille | title=Bastille | publisher=[[Official Charts Company]] | accessdate=12 April 2019}}\n* \"Poet\": {{cite web | url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/130309cluk.txt | title=Chart Log UK: New Entries Update \u2013 9.03.2013 (wk9) | publisher=Tobias Zywietz | work=zobbel.de | accessdate=14 March 2014 | author=Zywietz, Tobias}}\n* \"The Silence\": {{cite web | url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/130316cluk.txt | title=Chart Log UK: New Entries Update \u2013 16.03.2013 (wk10) | publisher=Tobias Zywietz | work=zobbel.de | accessdate=14 March 2014 | author=Zywietz, Tobias}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Ultratop|BEL]]<br><ref name=\"BEL-FL\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Dutch Top 40|NLD]]<br><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.top40.nl/top40/2017/week-51 | title=Nederlandse Top 40 \u2013 week 51, 2017  | work=top40.nl | accessdate=12 April 2019 | language=Dutch}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Sverigetopplistan|SWE]]<br><ref name=\"SWE\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Swiss Hitparade|SWI]]<br><ref name=\"SWI\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Alternative Songs|US<br>Alt.]]<br><ref name=\"US-Alternative-singles\">{{cite web |title=Bastille Chart History: Alternative Songs |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/bastille/chart-history/alternative-songs |website=Billboard |accessdate=10 July 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Billboard charts#Rock|US<br>Rock]]<br><ref name=\"US-Rock-singles\">{{cite web | url=https://www.billboard.com/music/bastille/chart-history/rock-songs | title=Bastille Chart History: Hot Rock Songs | work=Billboard | accessdate=28 October 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Poet\"\n| rowspan=\"5\"| 2013\n| 121 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| rowspan=\"5\"| ''All This Bad Blood''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"The Silence\"\n| 113 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"The Draw\"\n| 104 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[What Would You Do? (City High song)|What Would You Do?]]\"\n| 124 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Skulls\"\n| 169 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"bad_news\"\n| 2014\n| 98 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| ''VS. (Other People's Heartache, Pt. III)''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Fake It (Bastille song)|Fake It]]\"\n| 2016\n| 83 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014{{efn|group=upper-alpha|\"Fake It\" did not enter the Alternative Songs chart, but peaked at number 24 on the Alternative Digital Song Sales chart.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.billboard.com/biz/charts/2016-08-20/alternative-digital-songs | title=Alternative Digital Songs \u2013 August 20, 2016 | work=Billboard | accessdate=28 October 2018 |url-access=subscription }}</ref>}} || 28\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''Wild World''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Warmth\"\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2017\n| \u2014 || 52 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Basket Case (song)#Cover versions|Basket Case]]\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014{{efn|group=upper-alpha|\"Basket Case\" did not enter the Alternative Songs chart, but peaked at number 24 on the Alternative Digital Song Sales chart.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.billboard.com/biz/charts/2017-09-16/alternative-digital-songs | title=Alternative Digital Song Sales \u2013 September 16, 2017 | work=Billboard | accessdate=28 October 2018 |url-access=subscription }}</ref>}} || 49\n| ''[[The Tick (2016 TV series)|The Tick]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"World Gone Mad\"\n| 66 || 36 || 27 || 99 || 78 || 9 || 11\n| ''[[Bright (film)|Bright]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Bad Decisions\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2019\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || 50\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''Doom Days''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Another Place\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || 38\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Admit Defeat\"\n| 2020\n| \u2014 || 77 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| ''Doom Days (This Got Out of Hand)''\n|-\n| colspan=\"10\" style=\"font-size:90%\"| \"\u2014\" denotes a recording that did not chart or was not released in that territory.\n|}\n\n==Guest Appearances==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Other artist(s)\n! scope=\"col\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Won't Let You Go\"\n| 2019\n| [[Frenship]]\n| ''Vacation''\n|}\n\n==Music videos==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of music videos, showing year released and director\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:19em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:1em;\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Director(s)\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Overjoyed\"\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2012\n| Courtney Phillips<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.promonews.tv/2011/12/05/bastille-overjoyed-by-courtney-phillips/|title=Bastille \u2018Overjoyed\u2019 by Courtney Phillips|last=Knight|first=David|date=5 December 2011|accessdate=31 March 2013|publisher=PromoNews.tv}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Bad Blood\"\n| Olivier Groulx<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.renegademusic.co.uk/bastille-draws-bad-blood/ |title=Bastille Draws 'Bad Blood' |date=7 July 2012 |accessdate=31 March 2013 |publisher=Renegade Music |archivedate=9 January 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140109111055/http://www.renegademusic.co.uk/bastille-draws-bad-blood/ |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Flaws\"\n| Austin Peters<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.promonews.tv/2012/09/14/bastille-flaws-by-austin-peters/|title=Bastille \u2018Flaws\u2019 by Austin Peters \u2013 now signed to Forever Pictures|last=Brown|first=Jimmy|date=14 September 2012|accessdate=31 March 2013|publisher=PromoNews.tv}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Pompeii\"\n| rowspan=\"4\"| 2013\n| Jesse John Jenkins<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.promonews.tv/2013/03/07/bastille-pompeii-directors-cut-